        "payload": "tree 788ba3457f3c1a6b968089077ad8adf1400bf65b\nparent cad5f5604582eac95bcfbf08cca8af1c186c36eb\nauthor Hodlinator <172445034+hodlinator@users.noreply.github.com> 1779301996 +0200\ncommitter Hodlinator <172445034+hodlinator@users.noreply.github.com> 1779369335 +0200\n\ntest: Cover future chain-start MTP boundary in headers presync\n\nWhen the local clock sits more than `MAX_FUTURE_BLOCK_TIME` behind the chain-start MTP, the elapsed value used to derive `m_max_commitments` is negative.\nThe later division by the unsigned commitment period converts that negative value to a large unsigned bound.\nPresync ends up with A LOT of commitment slots, whereas it should abort.\n\nPin that pre-fix behavior in a regression test that the subsequent fix will alter.\n\nCo-authored-by: Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com>\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN SSH SIGNATURE-----\nU1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAg39Hzirivn9mM3G8qwAOGOKsmHT\ny2f/O2iDRQI8UxEyoAAAADZ2l0AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5\nAAAAQCDU2aAE/98EczKaDujk24otFtxcTleNhMdXyb7f5X+Vc8PD6ON/5ocYJGbzjSG3TV\nVLU+8vieih/6YTWH9Zaws=\n-----END SSH SIGNATURE-----"
      },
      "parents": [
        {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/cad5f5604582eac95bcfbf08cca8af1c186c36eb",
          "sha": "cad5f5604582eac95bcfbf08cca8af1c186c36eb",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/cad5f5604582eac95bcfbf08cca8af1c186c36eb"
        }
      ],
      "message": "test: Cover future chain-start MTP boundary in headers presync\n\nWhen the local clock sits more than `MAX_FUTURE_BLOCK_TIME` behind the chain-start MTP, the elapsed value used to derive `m_max_commitments` is negative.\nThe later division by the unsigned commitment period converts that negative value to a large unsigned bound.\nPresync ends up with A LOT of commitment slots, whereas it should abort.\n\nPin that pre-fix behavior in a regression test that the subsequent fix will alter.\n\nCo-authored-by: Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com>",
