      "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/db9c704117ea0e9125ee4f9bd9b26a8633b34df6",
      "tree": {
        "sha": "e487cbd2b34d10eac8d24a44ada23dfde88b88c5",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/e487cbd2b34d10eac8d24a44ada23dfde88b88c5"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree e487cbd2b34d10eac8d24a44ada23dfde88b88c5\nparent b0a2c0daf56ec0b8eba7e776abab07830ca9a032\nauthor Hodlinator <172445034+hodlinator@users.noreply.github.com> 1779364108 +0200\ncommitter Hodlinator <172445034+hodlinator@users.noreply.github.com> 1779369335 +0200\n\nnet: Throw exception from HeadersSyncState when system clock is behind start block MTP\n\nWe should not proceed syncing headers from peers when the local system clock is incorrectly set.\n\nA node with a system clock set too far back will typically fail early during startup when the chainstate detects the tip to be too far in the future. This means that in practice we don't expect the failure to ever happen in net_processing.cpp.\nOne can provoke the std::abort() in net_processing.cpp to happen through adding a call to SetMockTime(1) right before creating the HeadersSyncState.\n\nIssue discovered by: Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com>\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN SSH SIGNATURE-----\nU1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAg39Hzirivn9mM3G8qwAOGOKsmHT\ny2f/O2iDRQI8UxEyoAAAADZ2l0AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5\nAAAAQLBGKQUEQti8ON7fencY+3csl03SLtMgiEqIqZ+MaX75jT/zOSwAgoj6/FjmiWWLzO\nR5CI9/F9LdftkKDVduHAE=\n-----END SSH SIGNATURE-----"
      },
      "parents": [
        {
